oracle.spatial.rdf.client.jena

Class QueryOptions

  • java.lang.Object
    • oracle.spatial.rdf.client.jena.QueryOptions

  • public class QueryOptions
extends java.lang.Object
    This class allows the user to specify necessary options used by SDO_RDF_MATCH (or SEM_MATCH in 11g) so that queries against an inferred graph with INCOMPLETE or INVALID status can go through.

      • ALLOW_QUERY_INCOMPLETE_AND_DUP

        public static final QueryOptions ALLOW_QUERY_INCOMPLETE_AND_DUP
        A constant denoting that a query against an instance of GraphOracleSem can go through when the inferred graph has an INCOMPLETE status. Also, duplicates are not consolidated/merged when there are multiple models involved in a query.

      • ALLOW_QUERY_INVALID

        public static final QueryOptions ALLOW_QUERY_INVALID
        A constant denoting that a query against an instance of GraphOracleSem can go through even if the inferred graph has an INVALID status.

        public static final QueryOptions ALLOW_QUERY_INVALID_AND_DUP
        A constant denoting that a query against an instance of GraphOracleSem can go through even if the inferred graph has an INVALID status. Also, duplicates are not consolidated/merged when there are multiple models involved in a query.

      • ALLOW_QUERY_VALID_AND_DUP

        public static final QueryOptions ALLOW_QUERY_VALID_AND_DUP
        A constant denoting that a query against an instance of GraphOracleSem can go through only when the inferred graph has a VALID status. Also, duplicates are not consolidated/merged when there are multiple models involved in a query.

      • DEFAULT

        public static final QueryOptions DEFAULT
        A constant denoting that default option. It is the same as QUERY_VALID_ONLY.
